==== SOURCE

http://news.mit.edu/2019/using-machine-learning-hunt-down-cybercriminals-1009

==== AGENT

CSAIL & Center for Applied Internet Data Analysis

==== GOAL

To identify networks involved in IP hijacking

==== DATA

Data was retrieved from network operator mailing lists and historical BGP data taken every 5 minutes from the global routing table.

==== METHODS

Trained a classifier to automatically identify qualities of malicious behavior, such as volatile changes in activity, multiple address blocks and IP addresses in multiple countries.

==== RESULTS

False positives accounted for 20% of all networks identified as malicious.

==== COMMENTS

The article plays down how ineffective the classifier is.
